25:08.200 --> 25:12.360
in the steam tunnels under Michigan State University?

25:12.360 --> 25:14.720
No, there wasn't.

25:16.160 --> 25:24.500
There was a college student at University of Michigan, I've forgotten which it was,

25:28.540 --> 25:29.500
who disappeared,

25:30.780 --> 25:32.880
and his family couldn't find him.

25:32.980 --> 25:34.800
He was a Dungeons & Dragons player,

25:35.400 --> 25:37.940
and one of the things that the investigators,

25:38.120 --> 25:39.460
and they hired a private detective,

25:39.600 --> 25:42.080
family hired a private detective to try and locate him.

25:43.200 --> 25:46.580
One of the things that he found was a series of maps,

25:46.620 --> 25:49.120
which were probably Dungeons & Dragons maps,

25:49.280 --> 25:50.620
a lot of mysterious maps.

25:50.620 --> 25:53.180
And somebody suggested that they were maps

25:53.180 --> 25:55.920
of the steam tunnels underneath the university

25:55.920 --> 25:59.080
and that people had been playing Dungeons & Dragons

25:59.080 --> 26:00.080
in the steam tunnels.

26:01.980 --> 26:03.100
As far as I know,

26:03.180 --> 26:05.520
that's never really been proven to be the case,

26:05.520 --> 26:07.940
that anybody was actually playing in the steam tunnels.

26:08.240 --> 26:10.380
Anyway, he turned up alive.

26:11.660 --> 26:13.020
He showed up,

26:14.120 --> 26:17.540
and I think he had gone to visit some member of his family

26:17.540 --> 26:19.240
some distance away.

26:20.280 --> 26:22.400
And when there was enough publicity,

26:22.440 --> 26:24.480
there was a lot of publicity about this,

26:24.880 --> 26:29.560
a lot of television and radio news coverage of it

26:29.560 --> 26:30.580
when it occurred,

26:32.060 --> 26:33.240
partly, I think,

26:33.340 --> 26:37.460
because the news media people sensed

26:37.460 --> 26:40.020
that this was a weird cult,

26:40.180 --> 26:42.940
like the Jonestown massacre thing,

26:42.940 --> 26:44.880
which had occurred a year or so before.

26:45.640 --> 26:48.500
And they thought they were on to something really bizarre.

26:49.560 --> 26:51.060
But he turned up alive,

26:51.080 --> 26:54.560
and his disappearance had to do with his own personal life

26:54.560 --> 26:56.360
and his own personal problems, I guess,

26:56.400 --> 26:59.440
and had nothing to do with his playing Dungeons & Dragons.

27:01.040 --> 27:03.820
Another controversy that has brought some criticism of the game

27:03.820 --> 27:06.460
is the use of certain mythological creatures in the game.

27:06.660 --> 27:09.340
The game's fantasy element includes demons and devils

27:09.340 --> 27:11.560
based either on popular books or classical myths.

27:11.560 --> 27:14.880
The accusation usually is

27:14.880 --> 27:19.400
that the game is dangerous

27:19.400 --> 27:23.780
because it's actually teaching children.

27:24.180 --> 27:26.020
Of course, the people who are playing the game

27:26.020 --> 27:28.340
are frequently adults and not children,

27:28.340 --> 27:29.120
but, you know,

27:29.220 --> 27:32.980
it depends on what age you consider to be a child,

27:32.980 --> 27:34.580
and there certainly are plenty of people

27:34.580 --> 27:36.420
12 years old playing the game.

27:38.400 --> 27:41.120
teaching them, you know,

27:41.240 --> 27:45.860
the evil occult and demonological ritual.

27:46.900 --> 27:49.380
And the people who make these accusations,

27:49.540 --> 27:50.700
as it turns out,

27:50.840 --> 27:53.880
are extremely religious people,

27:54.100 --> 27:55.700
fundamentalist religious people,

27:55.700 --> 27:58.540
who really believe in the existence

27:58.540 --> 28:00.100
of the devil and his demons.

28:01.200 --> 28:04.980
The flap over the use of the game,

28:05.200 --> 28:10.500
particularly its use as a club in a high school

28:10.500 --> 28:11.560
or something like that,

28:11.760 --> 28:16.300
usually ends up to be involved with this controversy

28:16.300 --> 28:20.440
about how serious do you take demonology.

28:21.260 --> 28:23.360
And if you're serious about it,

28:23.480 --> 28:25.560
then you don't want to have it as a game

28:26.380 --> 28:28.360
or even as part of a game.

28:29.340 --> 28:31.220
These elements can be left out of the game

28:31.220 --> 28:33.100
if the people playing find it offensive.

28:33.460 --> 28:35.220
There are hundreds of other mythical creatures

28:35.220 --> 28:36.840
to test the mettle of any adventurer.

28:37.000 --> 28:39.300
The game's creators never intended Dungeons & Dragons

28:39.300 --> 28:40.960
to offend anyone's religious beliefs.

28:41.120 --> 28:42.740
They only wanted to bring to life

28:42.740 --> 28:43.680
the elements of fantasy

28:43.680 --> 28:45.360
that so many people enjoy in books

28:45.360 --> 28:46.240
like Lord of the Rings.

